Nice. But just some advice. you could go down to 300, or even 250Kbps and this would still be watchable. I've been testing on my own, and have been converting my avi video files down to Mkv. If I had a faster computer I'd convert to WebM. But I don't have an i3, i5, or i7. Just a semi decent Sony 1.6Ghz dual core. But I do see that you used  450Kbps, very nice. but you could go smaller than that, and it will still be decent quality. I've been using 250Kbps, but that's just me. If I were you, I'd go down to 300Kbps. Thanx for the download, I think I really like Supernatural, and have come here because you have used Mkv format, which by the next year, or year or so, everyone should start using the new Video Container Mkv with the Codec H.264. Better yet, Mkv with VP8 Codec, or the ULTIMATE WebM with VP8 Codec, INSANE Quality, and INSANE file Size. TINY.
